The study of ancient human evolution is one of the important contents of anthropology and ethnology. The study of ancient human evolution is usually based on: _____
A. Oral and traditional culture;
B. Folklore and fairy tales;
C. Archaeological and anthropological site research;
D. Documentation and historical records.

